parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission downshifting issues can cause loss of control, jerking, and sudden acceleration, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The transmission downshifts abruptly
causing the vehicle to jerk or surge forward
especially when driving down hills or inclines. The vehicle may lose traction on slippery roads
and the driver may experience a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission hesitation and slipping can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or slips when shifting gears
causing the vehicle to stall or lose power. The vehicle may roll backward or forward unexpectedly
and the driver may experience a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
and the vehicle may stall or lose power when shifting gears. The driver may experience difficulty shifting gears or the vehicle may roll backward or forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The speedometer and odometer failure can cause the driver to lose track of speed and distance, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The speedometer and odometer may malfunction
causing the driver to lose track of speed and distance. The driver may experience difficulty driving safely
especially at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Installing brake pads designed for smaller wheels on a vehicle with larger wheels can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes may not stop the vehicle properly
the brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
the brake pedal may stick to the floor
the vehicle may not respond to braking in emergency situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail completely, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle does not stop
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes may not respond to braking in emergency situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
there is a noise
extended stopping distance
the brakes may not respond to braking in emergency situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent brake failure can lead to accidents and injuries due to the unpredictability of the braking system.
symptoms: The brakes may fail intermittently
the brake pedal may go to the floor
the vehicle may not respond to braking in emergency situations
the brakes may not stop the vehicle properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bags to deploy in the event of an accident can increase the risk of injuries and fatalities.
symptoms: The air bags do not deploy in the event of an accident
the vehicle may not stop properly
the brakes may not respond to braking in emergency situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
vehicle surging forward
engine racing
difficulty stopping
hesitation when accelerating
speedometer malfunction or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning speedometer can lead to unsafe driving conditions, as the driver is unaware of their speed.
symptoms: Speedometer drops to zero intermittently
speedometer stops working altogether
speedometer starts and stops at will.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil leak and burning can cause smoke to come from the exhaust manifold, leading to a potential fire hazard and engine damage.
symptoms: Oil dripping from the filter onto the manifold
smoke coming from the exhaust manifold
burning smell
oil leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine, radiator, and other components, leading to costly repairs and potential engine failure.
symptoms: Temperature gauge rising above normal
smoke coming from the exhaust
engine dying
radiator fluid boiling over.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor engine performance can lead to hesitation, stalling, and loss of power, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Hesitation to accelerate
poor gas mileage
hesitation upon starting out
loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning air conditioning can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent or non-functional air conditioning.
